249 ff. Evidently Pampilus has never seen Cremes’ daughter; see on despondi (102).

249. nisi si: this pleonasm is rare in formal prose, but com- mon in colloquial Latin. The clause depends upon a nescio which is implied as the answer to the question Quam ob rem?
